# Walkthrough - Image Analysis Script (NLM, HOG, GLCM)

I have created a new Python script [nlm_hog_glcm_analysis.py](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/PycharmProjects/CARAT/nlm_hog_glcm_analysis.py) that provides a side-by-side analysis of a single image using three key techniques: **Non-Local Means (NLM) Denoising**, **Histogram of Oriented Gradients (HOG)**, and **Gray-Level Co-occurrence Matrix (GLCM)**.

## Changes Made

### [New Script]
#### [nlm_hog_glcm_analysis.py](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/PycharmProjects/CARAT/nlm_hog_glcm_analysis.py)
 - **NLM Denoising**: Smooths the image while preserving edges.
 - **HOG Visualization**: Highlights the orientation of gradients, useful for identifying shapes and structures (like tumor boundaries).
 - **GLCM Analysis**: Computes texture features (Contrast, Homogeneity, Energy, etc.) and provides a heatmap of the co-occurrence matrix.

